item.title: Master's project: Reliability Estimation in Series Systems
item.description: I presented my master’s project in October 2023. It was titled ‘Reliability Estimation in Series Systems: Maximum Likelihood Techniques for Right-Censored and Masked Failure Data’.

item.title: Model Selection in Weibull Series Systems
item.description: In my paper, Reliability Estimation in Series Systems, I discarded a lot of research that may be interesting to pursue further. This one is about using homogeneous shape parameters for the Weibull series system, which can greatly simplify the analysis and reduce the number of parameters to estimate. It’s also quite reasonable for most well-designed systems.
